# ── Email (Story 17) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave SMTP_HOST and SMTP_USER blank → Ethereal test account is used automatically.
# A preview URL is printed to the backend console after each order.
#
# To send real email via Gmail:
#   1. Enable 2-Step Verification on your Google account.
#   2. Go to: Google Account → Security → App Passwords → create one (name it "MAISON").
#      You get a 16-character password — use that as SMTP_PASS (no spaces).
#   3. Fill in all four fields below, then restart the backend.
#
# Gmail settings:
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=noreplymaisoncs308@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=kduv rxdt jhdw dyue
SMTP_FROM=noreplymaisoncs308@gmail.com
#
# Expected backend log when real SMTP is active:
#   [Email] Sending invoice INV-xxxx via real SMTP (smtp.gmail.com) …
#   [Email] Invoice sent via real SMTP to customer@example.com (messageId: …)
#
# Expected backend log when Ethereal is active (SMTP_USER or SMTP_HOST is blank):
